12/09/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- Newly-elected President Abdullah Gul on Tuesday (September 11th) visited the eastern city of Van -- the first stop in his five-city tour of Turkey's southeastern provinces.
The tour aims to send a message of unity to the residents of the region, where most of the country's Kurdish population lives.
In other news Tuesday, Washington announced that US Secretary of State Condoleezza Rice will visit Istanbul in late October for a meeting of Iraq's neighbours.
The meeting is being organised by Iraq and Turkey.
(Zaman, Anadolu news agency, Milliyet - 12/09/07;
NTV, Hurriyet, The New Anatolian, AFP - 11/09/07)
